{"title_page": "1992 United States presidential election in Hawaii", "text_new": "{{Main|1992 United States presidential election}}\n{{Infobox Election\n| election_name = 1992 [[United States presidential election]] in Hawaii\n| country = Hawaii\n| type = presidential\n| ongoing = no\n| previous_election = 1988 United States presidential election in Hawaii\n| previous_year = 1988\n| next_election = 1996 United States presidential election in Hawaii\n| next_year = 1996\n| election_date = November 3, 1992\n| image_size = x160px\n| image1 = Bill Clinton.jpg\n| nominee1 = '''[[Bill Clinton]]'''\n| party1 = Democratic Party (United States)\n| home_state1 = [[Arkansas]]\n| running_mate1 = '''[[Al Gore]]'''\n| electoral_vote1 = '''4'''\n| popular_vote1 = '''179,310'''\n| percentage1 = '''48.09%'''\t\n| image2 = George H. W. Bush presidential portrait (cropped 2).jpg\n| nominee2 = [[George H.W. Bush]] \n| party2 = Republican Party (United States)\n| home_state2 = [[Texas]]\n| running_mate2 = [[Dan Quayle]]\n| electoral_vote2 = 0\n| popular_vote2 = 136,822\n| percentage2 = 36.70%\t\n| image3 = RossPerotColor.jpg\n| nominee3 = [[Ross Perot]]\n| party3 = Independent (politician)\n| home_state3 = [[Texas]]\n| running_mate3 = [[James Stockdale]]\n| electoral_vote3 = 0\n| popular_vote3 = 53,003\t   \n| percentage3 = 14.22%\n| map_image = HI1992.jpg\n| map_size = 350px\n| map_caption = County Results\n'''Clinton'''\n{{legend|#b9d7ff|40\u201350%}}\n{{legend|#86b6f2|50\u201360%}}\n| title = President\n| before_election = [[George H. W. Bush]]\n| before_party = Republican Party (United States)\n| after_election = [[Bill Clinton]]\n| after_party = Democratic Party (United States)\n}}\n{{ElectionsHI}}\n\nThe '''1992 United States presidential election in Hawaii''' took place on November 3, 1992, as part of the [[1992 United States presidential election]]. Voters chose four representatives, or electors to the [[United States Electoral College|Electoral College]], who voted for [[President of the United States|president]] and [[Vice President of the United States|vice president]].\n\n[[Hawaii]] was won by Governor [[Bill Clinton]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]]-[[Arkansas]]) with 48.09% of the popular vote over incumbent President [[George H. W. Bush|George H.W. Bush]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|R]]-[[Texas]]) with 36.70%. Businessman [[Ross Perot]] ([[Independent politician|I]]-Texas) finished in third, with 14.22% of the popular vote, which was nonetheless Perot\u2019s poorest showing outside the District of Columbia and [[slave states and free states|antebellum slave states]].<ref name=results/> Clinton ultimately won the national vote, defeating incumbent President Bush. Clinton comfortably won Hawaii by a margin of 11.39%. It has only voted Republican twice since its statehood ([[1972 United States presidential election in Hawaii|1972]] for [[Richard Nixon]], and [[1984 United States presidential election in Hawaii|1984]] for [[Ronald Reagan]]). These Republican wins were landslides for Presidents Nixon and Reagan who both carried 49 out of 50 states. Hawaii has remained reliably Democratic since.<ref>{{cite web|title=1992 Presidential General Election Results|url=http://uselectionatlas.org/RESULTS/national.php?year=1992|publisher=U.S. Election Atlas|accessdate=8 June 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Results==\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|- style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"\n! colspan=\"6\" | 1992 United States presidential election in Hawaii<ref name=results>{{cite web|title=1992 Presidential General Election Results - Hawaii|url=http://uselectionatlas.org/RESULTS/state.php?year=1992&off=0&elect=0&fips=15&f=0|publisher=U.S. Election Atlas|accessdate=8 June 2012}}</ref>\n|-bgcolor=\"#EEEEEE\" align=\"center\"\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 15em\" |Party\n! style=\"width: 17em\" |Candidate\n! style=\"width: 5em\" |Votes\n! style=\"width: 7em\" |Percentage\n! style=\"width: 5em\" |Electoral votes\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#3333FF; width: 3px\" |\n| style=\"width: 130px\" | '''[[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]'''\n| '''[[Bill Clinton]]'''\n| align=\"right\" | '''179,310'''\n| align=\"right\" | '''48.09%'''\n| align=\"right\" | '''4'''\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#FF3333; width: 3px\" |\n| style=\"width: 130px\" | [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n| [[George H.W. Bush]] ([[incumbent]])\n| align=\"right\" | 136,822\n| align=\"right\" | 36.70%\n| align=\"right\" | 0\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#DDDDDD; width: 3px\" |\n| style=\"width: 130px\" | [[Independent (politician)|Independent]]\n| [[Ross Perot]]\n| align=\"right\" | 53,003\t\n| align=\"right\" | 14.22%\n| align=\"right\" | 0\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#FFA6C9; width: 3px\" |\n| style=\"width: 130px\" | [[Populist Party (United States, 1984)|America First]]\n| [[Bo Gritz|James \"Bo\" Gritz]]\n| align=\"right\" | 1,452\t\n| align=\"right\" | 0.39%\n| align=\"right\" | 0\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#FFCC00; width: 3px\" |\n| style=\"width: 130px\" | [[Libertarian Party (United States)|Libertarian]]\n| [[Andre Marrou]]\n| align=\"right\" | 1,119  \t\n| align=\"right\" | 0.30%\t\n| align=\"right\" | 0\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#FF00FF; width: 3px\" |\n| style=\"width: 130px\" | [[New Alliance Party]]\n| [[Lenora Fulani]]\n| align=\"right\" | 720 \t\t\n| align=\"right\" | 0.19%\n| align=\"right\" | 0\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#ffe4e1; width: 3px\" |\n| style=\"width: 130px\" | [[Natural Law Party|Natural Law]]\n| [[John Hagelin|Dr. John Hagelin]]\n| align=\"right\" | 416 \t\n| align=\"right\" | 0.11%\n| align=\"right\" | 0\n|-\n|-bgcolor=\"#EEEEEE\"\n| colspan=\"3\" align=\"right\" | '''Totals'''\n| align=\"right\" | '''372,842'''\n| align=\"right\" | '''100.0%'''\n| align=\"right\" | '''4'''\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{State Results of the 1992 U.S. presidential election}}\n{{United States elections, 1992}}\n[[Category:1992 United States presidential election by state|Hawaii]]\n[[Category:United States presidential elections in Hawaii|1992]]\n[[Category:1992 Hawaii elections]]\n", "text_old": "{{Main|1992 United States presidential election}}\n{{Infobox Election\n| election_name = 1992 [[United States presidential election]] in Hawaii\n| country = Hawaii\n| type = presidential\n| ongoing = no\n| previous_election = 1988 United States presidential election in Hawaii\n| previous_year = 1988\n| next_election = 1996 United States presidential election in Hawaii\n| next_year = 1996\n| election_date = November 3, 1992\n| image_size = x160px\n| image1 = Bill Clinton.jpg\n| nominee1 = '''[[Bill Clinton]]'''\n| party1 = Democratic Party (United States)\n| home_state1 = [[Arkansas]]\n| running_mate1 = '''[[Al Gore]]'''\n| electoral_vote1 = '''4'''\n| popular_vote1 = '''179,310'''\n| percentage1 = '''48.09%'''\t\n| image2 = George H. W. Bush, President of the United States, 1989 official portrait (cropped 2).jpg\n| nominee2 = [[George H.W. Bush]] \n| party2 = Republican Party (United States)\n| home_state2 = [[Texas]]\n| running_mate2 = [[Dan Quayle]]\n| electoral_vote2 = 0\n| popular_vote2 = 136,822\n| percentage2 = 36.70%\t\n| image3 = RossPerotColor.jpg\n| nominee3 = [[Ross Perot]]\n| party3 = Independent (politician)\n| home_state3 = [[Texas]]\n| running_mate3 = [[James Stockdale]]\n| electoral_vote3 = 0\n| popular_vote3 = 53,003\t   \n| percentage3 = 14.22%\n| map_image = HI1992.jpg\n| map_size = 350px\n| map_caption = County Results\n'''Clinton'''\n{{legend|#b9d7ff|40\u201350%}}\n{{legend|#86b6f2|50\u201360%}}\n| title = President\n| before_election = [[George H. W. Bush]]\n| before_party = Republican Party (United States)\n| after_election = [[Bill Clinton]]\n| after_party = Democratic Party (United States)\n}}\n{{ElectionsHI}}\n\nThe '''1992 United States presidential election in Hawaii''' took place on November 3, 1992, as part of the [[1992 United States presidential election]]. Voters chose four representatives, or electors to the [[United States Electoral College|Electoral College]], who voted for [[President of the United States|president]] and [[Vice President of the United States|vice president]].\n\n[[Hawaii]] was won by Governor [[Bill Clinton]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]]-[[Arkansas]]) with 48.09% of the popular vote over incumbent President [[George H. W. Bush|George H.W. Bush]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|R]]-[[Texas]]) with 36.70%. Businessman [[Ross Perot]] ([[Independent politician|I]]-Texas) finished in third, with 14.22% of the popular vote, which was nonetheless Perot\u2019s poorest showing outside the District of Columbia and [[slave states and free states|antebellum slave states]].<ref name=results/> Clinton ultimately won the national vote, defeating incumbent President Bush. Clinton comfortably won Hawaii by a margin of 11.39%. It has only voted Republican twice since its statehood ([[1972 United States presidential election in Hawaii|1972]] for [[Richard Nixon]], and [[1984 United States presidential election in Hawaii|1984]] for [[Ronald Reagan]]). These Republican wins were landslides for Presidents Nixon and Reagan who both carried 49 out of 50 states. Hawaii has remained reliably Democratic since.<ref>{{cite web|title=1992 Presidential General Election Results|url=http://uselectionatlas.org/RESULTS/national.php?year=1992|publisher=U.S. Election Atlas|accessdate=8 June 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Results==\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|- style=\"background-color:#E9E9E9\"\n! colspan=\"6\" | 1992 United States presidential election in Hawaii<ref name=results>{{cite web|title=1992 Presidential General Election Results - Hawaii|url=http://uselectionatlas.org/RESULTS/state.php?year=19