freemium products \u2013 like WebEx or Cisco Spark \u2013 which have versions that users can use for free. Thus, while H.265 is still a good fit for hardware products like our telepresence room systems, it is not something that can serve as a universal video codec across hardware and software. Thus, we believe the industry needs a high quality, next-generation codec that can be used everywhere.}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"moz-avc-reluctance\">{{cite web|url=https://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2012/03/mozilla-firefox-needs-h264-support-to-survive-shift-to-mobile|title=Firefox needs H.264 support to survive shift to mobile|date=19 March 2012|accessdate=15 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"hevc-2015\">{{cite web |url=https://www.streamingmedia.com/Articles/Editorial/Featured-Articles/HEVCs-Journey-in-2015-Going-Downhill-and-Gaining-Speed-107891.aspx|title=HEVC's Journey in 2015: Going Downhill and Gaining Speed|date=1 December 2015|accessdate=16 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"cnet-1050\">{{cite web |last1=Shankland |first1=Stephen |title=Streaming video could be saddled with a new patent licensing cost |url=https://www.cnet.com/news/patent-group-wants-a-new-toll-on-the-streaming-video-road/ |quote=Sisvel begins selling licenses for more than 1,050 patents for AV1, a video technology that's supposed to be free. |website=CNET |accessdate=15 March 2020 |date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|AOMedia Video 1|AV1}}\n* [https://aomediacodec.github.io/av1-spec/av1-spec.pdf AV1 Bitstream and decoding process specification]\n* [https://github.com/AOMediaCodec AOMedia GitHub organization]\n* [https://aomedia.googlesource.com/ Source code repository]\n* [https://aomedia-review.googlesource.com/ Source code review]\n* [https://bugs.chromium.org/p/aomedia Issue tracker]\n* [https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-netvc-requirements Requirements] to be met for the IETF NetVC\n* [https://caniuse.com/#feat=av1 Browser availability table for AV1 on caniuse]\n\n{{Compression formats}}\n\n[[Category:Computer-related introductions in 2018]]\n[[Category:Film and video technology]]\n[[Category:Free video codecs]]\n[[Category:Lossy compression algorithms]]\n[[Category:Open formats]]\n[[Category:Video compression]]\n[[Category:Videotelephony]]\n", "name_user": "Aasami", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAVIF support", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AV1"}
